track_strategy:
Braking points must be extended significantly, utilizing engine braking as the primary deceleration method to prevent lock-up. Apply minimal throttle percentage in the highest feasible gear to mitigate wheelspin on corner exit. A wide, constant radius line is required to minimize steering input and avoid inducing slip angle.

A track temperature delta of ±10°C is sub-critical as the compound is outside its thermal window; maintain current parameters. In the event of increased precipitation, box immediately for the extreme wet compound. Accelerated degradation is improbable, but monitor for cold tearing and report any surface aberrations.
